Reasoning: The paper investigates the performance of a wireless communication technology, specifically non-orthogonal multiple access (NOMA), which falls under the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT), communication (cs.COMM), and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also considers power allocation for achieving fairness and minimizing average BER, which falls under the sub-categories of systems and control (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM).
